---
// dog-training-classes.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const registrationLink = "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdsBjQdPSqAgzqrLwaPaKG2dyvewv_a1sDMxIK1Vvp8/edit?usp=sharing";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <article>
    <h2>Dog Training Classes</h2>
    <p>
      Animal Assisted Therapy Services (AATS) MA provides structured,
      high-quality community dog training classes designed to build foundational
      behavior, obedience, and strong human-canine partnerships. Their programs
      include the AKC S.T.A.R. Puppy course, which focuses on early
      socialization, basic obedience, and responsible pet ownership. They also
      offer an Intermediate Obedience class that mixes training center lessons
      with public field trips to teach handlers how to manage commands under
      real-world distractions. Finally, their AKC Canine Good Citizen course
      serves as an advanced obedience pipeline, thoroughly preparing dog teams
      to remain calm, welcoming, and well-behaved in diverse community and crowd
      settings.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
